RACE.RACE_TEXT: CANTERBURY PARK RACE 1 6 1/2F Dirt CR: 69. Maiden Claiming Purse 10500. FOR MAIDENS, FILLIES AND MARES THREE, FOUR, AND FIVE YEARS OLD. Three Year Olds, 119 lbs.; Older, 124 lbs. Claiming Price $10,000. Minnesota Bred Claiming Price $15,000.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: PURRFECT MOON brushed with the horse to her inside leaving the gate, pressed the pace between horses up the backstretch, dueled from the three path coming around the turn, kicked clear with a furlong to go and just held off a closer to the wire. JERUSALEMA (IRE) trailed the field up the backstretch, raced in the three path around the turn, began a bid passing the quarter pole and gained ground late to just miss. GRANDIOSE SUMMER tracked the pace setters between horses through the early going, came around the bend in the four path and chased the winner home in the lane. DIXIE GIRL TO dueled on the inside up the backstretch, continued to battle from the two path around the turn and in upper stretch and gave way in the final sixteenth of a mile. PAT'S GAL brushed with the horse to her outside at the start, recovered to chase the leaders between horses up the backstretch, came around the bend in the two path and was outkicked in the lane. SMART LEAH dueled on the outside through the opening quarter of a mile, navigated the turn from the five path and tired in the stretch. SKEDADDLE'S LEGACY raced off the pace through the opening stages, saved ground around the bend and was empty in the lane.
